        <infon key="n">2</infon>
        <offset>55</offset>
        <text>Drylands constitute the most extensive terrestrial biome, covering more than one-third of the Earth's continental surface.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">3</infon>
        <offset>178</offset>
        <text>In these environments, stress limits animal and plant life, so life forms that can survive desiccation and then resume growth following subsequent wetting assume the foremost role in ecosystem processes.
</text>
